omments, that I have tarried, in my distress and disappointment, on the brink of falsification. I must ask the reader to ignore those two lines (which, I am afraid, do not even scan properly). I could strike them out before publication but that would mean reworking the entire note, or at least a considerable part of it, and I have no time for such stupidities.





Lines 557-558; How to locate in blackness, with a gasp, Terra the Fair, an orbicle of jasp


The loveliest couplet in this canto.


